						               													<description>Villain VS is not a fair strategy game to have fun with your friends and family. I created the game and its backstory to test those who are truly obsessed with winning at all cost. Anyone can win a game with rules, heroes and endless comparable references.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;What if winning meant you had to be the worst and not the best? What if your desire to win was more important than your skill or luck? Well now you can find out.  Can you capture and tame the worst Villains from our Realm and use them to survive till the end and beat your opponents? It won't be easy but it will be rewarding when you manipulate, cheat, lie, beg, borrow and steal your way to a victory in Villain VS.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Villain VS is a cutthroat, win at all cost challenge to any serious strategist to test their true skill in a game that requires you to work with and against other players for a chance to survive till the end and win the game. VVS is not meant to be a fair game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players deal and trade Evidence Cards in the first stage until they have the enough of the required Evidence Cards to capture an escaped Villain Card and build their Villain Teams.  Once all players have a completed Villain Team the Battle Stage starts. Players battle their Villains against the other player's Villain Teams until only one Team or Villain remains.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who survives till the end wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;There is a companion Journal called &amp;quot;Journal #27 Creating VVS &amp;amp; The Singularity&amp;quot; explaining the history of the Game and its creation by Dr. Penelope I. Primrose High Priestess Coven of The Eternal and why she chose to trap the evil that bore our realm it's worst Villains.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
